"title": "2224: Jesus Christ, the Lord",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2224: jesus christ, the lord",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A title that signifies Jesus Christ's absolute authority and the basis on which people may know him. It is especially associated with his resurrection and return.</p>\n<h2>Lord as a title of respect for the earthly Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:25\">MAT 8:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:25\">MAT 15:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:27\">MAT 15:27</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:28\">MRK 7:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:3\">MAT 21:3</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:3\">MRK 11:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:31\">LUK 19:31</a></p>\n<h2>Lord as a mark of Jesus Christ's authority as a teacher</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:15\">1TH 4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:16\">ACT 11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:35\">ACT 20:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:10\">1CO 7:10</a></p>\n<h2>Lord as a sign of Jesus Christ's divinity</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's divinity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:28\">JHN 20:28</a></strong> <em>“Lord” is a common divine title in the Greek OT and is instinctively transferred to Jesus Christ in the NT.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:17-2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:17–3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:5\">EPH 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:16\">2TH 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:2\">2PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The day of Christ Jesus</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:6\">PHP 1:6</a></strong> <em>The “day of Christ Jesus” is equivalent to the OT “day of the LORD”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:8\">1CO 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:14\">2CO 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:10\">PHP 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:16\">PHP 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:10\">REV 1:10</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is ruler over all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:14\">REV 17:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:17\">DEU 10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:16\">REV 19:16</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the Saviour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:13\">ROM 10:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:32\">JOL 2:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:21\">ACT 2:21</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is Lord of the Sabbath</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:8\">MAT 12:8</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:28\">MRK 2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:5\">LUK 6:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus the Messiah is Lord</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:36\">ACT 2:36</a></strong> <em>“Christ” is the Greek equivalent of the Hebrew word “Messiah”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:5\">2CO 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:24\">COL 3:24</a></p>\n<h3>``Jesus is Lord'' is the basic Christian statement of faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:9\">ROM 10:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:20\">ACT 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:31\">ACT 16:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:21\">ACT 20:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:3\">1CO 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:5\">2CO 4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:10-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:10–2:11</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus is Lord because of the resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:33\">ACT 4:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:24\">ROM 4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:9\">ROM 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:20\">HEB 13:20</a></p>\n<h3>Lord is a natural title for the risen Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:34\">LUK 24:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:61\">LUK 22:61</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21\">ACT 1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:59\">ACT 7:59</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:1\">1CO 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:5\">1CO 9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's lordship is the basis for his relationship with Christians</h2>\n<h3>It is a personal relationship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:8\">PHP 3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:15\">ACT 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:11\">ROM 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:8\">ROM 14:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:17\">1CO 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:20\">2PE 2:20</a></p>\n<h3>``The name of the Lord'' expresses this relationship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:11\">1CO 6:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:16\">ACT 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:26\">ACT 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:5\">ACT 19:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:13\">ACT 21:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:20\">EPH 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:17\">COL 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>``Jesus our Lord'' expresses this relationship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:24\">EPH 6:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:57\">1CO 15:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:9\">2CO 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14\">GAL 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:20\">EPH 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:28\">1TH 5:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:8\">2TI 1:8</a></p>\n<h3>``In the Lord'' as an expression of this relationship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:16\">PHM 1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:12\">ROM 16:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:10\">EPH 6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:14\">PHP 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:29\">PHP 2:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:1\">PHP 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:20\">PHM 1:20</a></p>\n<h3>The ``grace of the Lord'' as God's provision for this relationship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:14\">1TI 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:14\">2CO 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:18\">2TH 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:25\">PHM 1:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:21\">JUD 1:21</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's lordship is the basis for Christian obedience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:6\">COL 2:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:11\">ROM 12:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:23\">COL 3:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:8\">2TH 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:19\">2TI 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:15\">1PE 3:15</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's lordship will be fully revealed</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:16\">1TH 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:7\">1CO 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20\">PHP 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:23\">1TH 5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:7\">2TH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:14\">1TI 6:14</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's lordship signifies his absolute authority</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as judge of all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:4\">1CO 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:32\">1CO 11:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:18\">2CO 10:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:6\">1TH 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:8-2Thess1:9\">2TH 1:8–1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as Lord of all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:12\">ROM 10:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:36\">ACT 10:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:10-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:10–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16-Col1:17\">COL 1:16–1:17</a></p>",
